# Frontend Patterns

## Component Props
```typescript
interface Props {
  items: Item[]
}

export function MyComponent({ items }: Readonly<Props>) {
  return <div>{/* ... */}</div>
}
```

## HTML Element Props
```typescript
interface ButtonProps extends ComponentProps<'button'> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary'
}
```

## Key Rules
1. Wrap props in `Readonly<Props>` (only when has props)
2. Use `ComponentProps<'element'>` for HTML elements
3. No props interface for components without props
4. Check existing components before creating new

## React Compiler
- No manual `useMemo`/`useCallback`
- Compiler handles optimization automatically

## Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only
- Never use inline `style={{}}`
- Custom CSS classes for complex animations

## Data Fetching
- tRPC for API calls
- Server components for initial data
- Client components for interactivity
